The International Skating Union (ISU) unveiled the complete competition schedule for the 2022-23 season on Wednesday. For the adult group, the ISU Grand Prix starts at Skate America on October 21, followed by stops in Canada, France and Japan, with the locations of two other legs undecided. The season finale will take place in Torino, Italy, from December 8 to 11. The junior skaters' seven-stop season starts in France on August 24 and ends on October 15 in Italy. The ISU also announced the details of two other major events. Japan's Saitama will host the 2023 World Figure Skating Championships from March 20 to 26, while the Four Continents International Championships will take place in Australia a month before the worlds. According to the ISU, cancellation, postponement, or venue changes could happen at any time to all the listed competitions this year due to COVID-19 concerns. (With input from Xinhua)